d:["$","article",null,{"className":"bg-white","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-6","children":["$","nav",null,{"className":"flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-gray-600","children":[["$","$L5",null,{"href":"/","className":"hover:text-blue-600","children":"Home"}],[["$","div","/car-seats",{"className":"flex items-center space-x-2","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-gray-400","children":"/"}],["$","$L5",null,{"href":"/car-seats","className":"hover:text-blue-600","children":"Car Seats"}]]}],["$","div","/car-seats/infant-vs-convertible-car-seat",{"className":"flex items-center space-x-2","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-gray-400","children":"/"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-gray-900 font-medium","children":"Infant vs Convertible Car Seats: Which Should You Buy First?"}]]}]]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 border-b border-gray-200","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4","children":"Infant vs Convertible Car Seats: Which Should You Buy First?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg text-gray-600","children":"Compare infant car seats and convertible car seats. Learn about safety, convenience, cost, and durability to decide which is right for your family."}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700","children":[["$","h2","0",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Introduction"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"When preparing for a newborn, one of the earliest decisions is selecting a car seat. Two main paths emerge: purchase a dedicated infant car seat for the first 6-12 months, then transition to a convertible car seat for years 2-8, or buy a convertible car seat upfront and skip the infant seat entirely. Each approach offers distinct advantages and trade-offs affecting cost, convenience, safety, and family dynamics."}],["$","h2","2",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Infant Car Seats"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"An infant car seat is designed specifically for newborns and small infants, typically supporting children from 4-35 lbs (ages 0-12 months). These seats are smaller, lighter, and more portable than convertible seats."}],["$","h2","4",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"#How Infant Seats Work"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"Infant seats function as standalone units that detach from their base with one hand. Many models are compatible with stroller frames, allowing you to move a sleeping baby between car and stroller without waking them. The seat itself slides into the car with a LATCH connector or vehicle seatbelt, then pops back out for transport."}],["$","h2","6",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"#Advantages of Infant Seats"}],["$","ul","7",{"className":"list-disc list-inside my-4 space-y-1","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"text-gray-700","children":"**Portability** — Detachable design lets you move sleeping babies without disturbance"}],["$","li","1",{"className":"text-gray-700","children":"**Stroller compatibility** — Creates a travel system; many infant seats work with major stroller brands"}],["$","li","2",{"className":"text-gray-700","children":"**Easier loading** — Lower profile makes buckling a newborn simpler than convertible seats"}],["$","li","3",{"className":"text-gray-700","children":"**Ease of installation** — LATCH installation typically requires fewer steps"}],"$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18"]}],"$L19","$L1a","$L1b","$L1c","$L1d","$L1e","$L1f","$L20","$L21","$L22","$L23","$L24","$L25","$L26","$L27","$L28","$L29","$L2a","$L2b","$L2c","$L2d","$L2e","$L2f","$L30","$L31","$L32","$L33","$L34","$L35","$L36","$L37","$L38","$L39","$L3a","$L3b","$L3c","$L3d","$L3e","$L3f","$L40","$L41","$L42","$L43","$L44","$L45","$L46","$L47"]}]}],"$L48","$L49"]}]
