2e:["$","p","29",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Cost difference:** $300 upfront for infant + convertible vs $300 for convertible alone. However, the infant + convertible path includes a portable, travel-system-compatible seat—which adds convenience value beyond raw cost."}]
2f:["$","h2","30",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Extended Rear-Facing: The Safety Advantage"}]
30:["$","p","31",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"Research strongly supports extended rear-facing (3+ years instead of 1 year). A child's neck and spine are fragile; rear-facing supports the head-and-neck during frontal collisions (the most common crash type), reducing injury risk by up to 75%."}]
31:["$","p","32",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Infant seats:** Rear-facing only; limited to 12 months."}]
32:["$","p","33",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Convertible seats:** Rear-facing until 3-4 years (if weight/height permit), a 2-3 year advantage."}]
33:["$","p","34",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"If extended rear-facing is a priority, convertible seats are essential. Infant seats cannot provide this benefit alone."}]
34:["$","h2","35",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Making the Decision: Key Questions"}]
35:["$","p","36",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"1. **How many vehicles will use the car seat regularly?**\n   - Multiple vehicles → Infant seat + bases for each car\n   - One primary car → Convertible seat"}]
36:["$","p","37",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"2. **Will you have multiple children soon?**\n   - Yes, 2+ children → Infant + convertible (travel system valuable)\n   - No, one child only → Convertible (lower total cost)"}]
37:["$","p","38",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"3. **Do you travel frequently by air?**\n   - Yes → Infant seat (easier TSA checkpoint passage)\n   - No → Either option works"}]
38:["$","p","39",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"4. **Is extended rear-facing important to you?**\n   - Yes → Convertible required\n   - No → Either option acceptable"}]
39:["$","p","40",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"5. **Do you use childcare or rely on caregivers?**\n   - Frequently → Infant seat (familiar to providers, less training)\n   - Rarely → Either option"}]
3a:["$","p","41",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"6. **What's your budget?**\n   - Tight ($300-350) → Convertible only\n   - Flexible ($600+) → Infant + convertible"}]
3b:["$","h2","42",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Hybrid Approach: Best of Both Worlds"}]
3c:["$","p","43",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"Some families use a hybrid strategy: purchase an infant seat with stroller travel system for the first year, prioritizing convenience and portability. When approaching the 12-month mark, invest in a premium convertible seat for extended rear-facing through age 3-4."}]
3d:["$","p","44",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Cost:** Infant seat ($300) + premium convertible ($400-450) = $700-750"}]
3e:["$","p","45",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Benefit:** Travel system convenience for the first year, plus 3 additional years of extended rear-facing safety."}]
3f:["$","p","46",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"This approach suits families who value both infant convenience and long-term safety but have flexibility in budget."}]
40:["$","h2","47",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Practical Installation Tips"}]
41:["$","p","48",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Infant seats:** Test-fit the seat in each vehicle before purchase. Some infant seats are too narrow for certain vehicle rows; others too bulky for compact cars."}]
42:["$","p","49",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Convertible seats:** Ensure your vehicle has LATCH points and sufficient space for reclined rear-facing installation (typically requires 28-30 inches of front-to-back space)."}]
43:["$","p","50",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Both:** Visit a local NHTSA-certified car seat technician for installation verification. Incorrect installation is the #1 reason safety is compromised."}]
44:["$","h2","51",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"The Bottom Line"}]
45:["$","p","52",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Choose infant + convertible if:** You want a travel system, have multiple vehicles, value portability, or are planning 2+ children in close succession."}]
46:["$","p","53",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Choose convertible only if:** You prioritize cost savings, have one primary car, value extended rear-facing safety, and prefer simplicity."}]
47:["$","p","54",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"Neither choice is \"wrong\"—both paths are safe when properly installed. Your decision should reflect your family's lifestyle, budget, and priorities around convenience vs long-term investment."}]
